increased to 79.2 billion meticais ($3 billion) in 2011 from
63.4 billion meticais a year earlier,  o Pais reported , citing
Rosario Fernandes, chairman of the national tax collector known
as Autoridade Tributaria.  The tax authority registered 322,835 new taxpayers during
the year, more than the 301,633 planned for 2011, the Maputo-
based newspaper reported. Mozambique has 1,544,119 registered
tax payers compared with 391,000 in 2006, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
